&lt;body&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;content&quot;&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;outline-container-org1ad99cf&quot; class=&quot;outline-2&quot;&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;org1ad99cf&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;section-number-2&quot;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; GNU/Linux&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;outline-text-2&quot; id=&quot;text-1&quot;&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;outline-container-org58a0fba&quot; class=&quot;outline-3&quot;&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;org58a0fba&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;section-number-3&quot;&gt;1.1&lt;/span&gt; Emacs keybindings everywhere&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;outline-text-3&quot; id=&quot;text-1-1&quot;&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;outline-container-org98e11f2&quot; class=&quot;outline-4&quot;&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;org98e11f2&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;section-number-4&quot;&gt;1.1.1&lt;/span&gt; GTK&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;outline-text-4&quot; id=&quot;text-1-1-1&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/GTK+#Emacs_key_bindings&quot;&gt;https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/GTK+#Emacs_key_bindings&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ol class=&quot;org-ol&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a id=&quot;org7dcb9f2&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Gtk3&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;outline-text-5&quot; id=&quot;text-1-1-1-1&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
$ gsettings set org.gnome.desktop.interface gtk-key-theme &amp;ldquo;Emacs&amp;rdquo;
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
If you have Anaconda installed, make sure your path points to your system gsettings not Anaconda’s gsettings.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a id=&quot;org7ac314f&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Gtk2&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;outline-text-5&quot; id=&quot;text-1-1-1-2&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;org-src-container&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;src src-bash&quot;&gt;gconftool-2 --type=string --set /desktop/gnome/interface/gtk_key_theme Emacs
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
~/.gtkrc-2.0
gtk-key-theme-name = &amp;ldquo;Emacs&amp;rdquo;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a id=&quot;orgec2b1cd&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;XFCE&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;outline-text-5&quot; id=&quot;text-1-1-1-3&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
$ xfconf-query -c xsettings -p /Gtk/KeyThemeName -s Emacs
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;outline-container-orga16da15&quot; class=&quot;outline-4&quot;&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;orga16da15&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;section-number-4&quot;&gt;1.1.2&lt;/span&gt; Chromium/Google Chrome&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;outline-text-4&quot; id=&quot;text-1-1-2&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
in “/home/zds/.config/gtk-3.0/settings.ini/” add this line:
gtk-key-theme-name=Emacs
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;outline-container-orgb4d15b6&quot; class=&quot;outline-3&quot;&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;orgb4d15b6&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;section-number-3&quot;&gt;1.2&lt;/span&gt; Desktop environment&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;outline-text-3&quot; id=&quot;text-1-2&quot;&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;outline-container-orge185907&quot; class=&quot;outline-4&quot;&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;orge185907&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;section-number-4&quot;&gt;1.2.1&lt;/span&gt; Xfce&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;outline-container-org47202ea&quot; class=&quot;outline-3&quot;&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;org47202ea&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;section-number-3&quot;&gt;1.3&lt;/span&gt; Emacs&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;outline-text-3&quot; id=&quot;text-1-3&quot;&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;outline-container-orgdc2bd0b&quot; class=&quot;outline-4&quot;&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;orgdc2bd0b&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;section-number-4&quot;&gt;1.3.1&lt;/span&gt; recommended compilation flags&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;outline-container-orgb0ee802&quot; class=&quot;outline-3&quot;&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;orgb0ee802&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;section-number-3&quot;&gt;1.4&lt;/span&gt; Terminal emulator&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;outline-container-org4692762&quot; class=&quot;outline-3&quot;&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;org4692762&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;section-number-3&quot;&gt;1.5&lt;/span&gt; Shell&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;outline-text-3&quot; id=&quot;text-1-5&quot;&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;outline-container-org3b42b47&quot; class=&quot;outline-4&quot;&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;org3b42b47&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;section-number-4&quot;&gt;1.5.1&lt;/span&gt; bash&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;outline-container-org17a795f&quot; class=&quot;outline-4&quot;&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;org17a795f&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;section-number-4&quot;&gt;1.5.2&lt;/span&gt; zsh&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;outline-container-org0315da3&quot; class=&quot;outline-3&quot;&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;org0315da3&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;section-number-3&quot;&gt;1.6&lt;/span&gt; input devicess&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;outline-text-3&quot; id=&quot;text-1-6&quot;&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;outline-container-orgdcf56a6&quot; class=&quot;outline-4&quot;&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;orgdcf56a6&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;section-number-4&quot;&gt;1.6.1&lt;/span&gt; keyboard&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;outline-text-4&quot; id=&quot;text-1-6-1&quot;&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ol class=&quot;org-ol&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a id=&quot;org2957f6c&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;fast repeat, low repeat delay&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;outline-text-5&quot; id=&quot;text-1-6-1-1&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
$ xset r rate [delay ms] [rate]
Recommended: xset r rate 160 180
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;outline-container-org5eae125&quot; class=&quot;outline-4&quot;&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;org5eae125&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;section-number-4&quot;&gt;1.6.2&lt;/span&gt; mouse&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;outline-text-4&quot; id=&quot;text-1-6-2&quot;&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ol class=&quot;org-ol&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a id=&quot;org73595bb&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;high acceleration&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;outline-container-org9076347&quot; class=&quot;outline-2&quot;&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;org9076347&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;section-number-2&quot;&gt;2&lt;/span&gt; macOS&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;outline-text-2&quot; id=&quot;text-2&quot;&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;outline-container-org88ee032&quot; class=&quot;outline-3&quot;&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;org88ee032&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;section-number-3&quot;&gt;2.1&lt;/span&gt; input devices&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;outline-text-3&quot; id=&quot;text-2-1&quot;&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;outline-container-orgc7e5f7a&quot; class=&quot;outline-4&quot;&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;orgc7e5f7a&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;section-number-4&quot;&gt;2.1.1&lt;/span&gt; keyboard&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;outline-text-4&quot; id=&quot;text-2-1-1&quot;&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ol class=&quot;org-ol&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a id=&quot;org96c15bc&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;fast repeat, low repeat delay&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;outline-text-5&quot; id=&quot;text-2-1-1-1&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
$ defaults write -g KeyRepeat -int 1
$ defaults write -g InitialKeyRepeat -int 10
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;outline-container-orgcb478b8&quot; class=&quot;outline-3&quot;&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;orgcb478b8&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;section-number-3&quot;&gt;2.2&lt;/span&gt; Emacs&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;outline-text-3&quot; id=&quot;text-2-2&quot;&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;outline-container-org9be40f1&quot; class=&quot;outline-4&quot;&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;org9be40f1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;section-number-4&quot;&gt;2.2.1&lt;/span&gt; Emacs Daemon&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;outline-text-4&quot; id=&quot;text-2-2-1&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
These instructions work as of macOS High Sierra (version 10.14) to run Emacs as a daemon on login. You can quickly run emacsclient instances without waiting for Emacs to start up.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ol class=&quot;org-ol&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a id=&quot;orgdd46d7c&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Create an Apple Script with “Script Editor.app”&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;outline-text-5&quot; id=&quot;text-2-2-1-1&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
~/Applications/Emacs Daemon.app:
do shell script &amp;ldquo;/Applications/Emacs.app/Contents/MacOS/Emacs &amp;#x2013;daemon&amp;rdquo;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a id=&quot;org3226741&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Add “Emacs Daemon.app&amp;ldquo; to autostart.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;outline-text-5&quot; id=&quot;text-2-2-1-2&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
System Preferences → Users &amp;amp; Groups → choose your user → Login Items
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a id=&quot;org6a77928&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Create an Apple Script for the client.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;outline-text-5&quot; id=&quot;text-2-2-1-3&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
“~/Applications/Emacs Client.app”:
do shell script &amp;ldquo;/Applications/Emacs.app/Contents/MacOS/bin/emacsclient -nc&amp;rdquo;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;outline-container-org3e17628&quot; class=&quot;outline-2&quot;&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;org3e17628&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;section-number-2&quot;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt; Windows&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;outline-text-2&quot; id=&quot;text-3&quot;&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;outline-container-org93fce42&quot; class=&quot;outline-3&quot;&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;org93fce42&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;section-number-3&quot;&gt;3.1&lt;/span&gt; keyboard repeat speed&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;outline-text-3&quot; id=&quot;text-3-1&quot;&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;outline-container-orgacfb0d6&quot; class=&quot;outline-4&quot;&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;orgacfb0d6&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;section-number-4&quot;&gt;3.1.1&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;todo TODO&quot;&gt;TODO&lt;/span&gt; find and publish the source of that Windows.h-calling code that changes keyboard repeat speed on Windows&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;outline-container-orgf53b937&quot; class=&quot;outline-2&quot;&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;orgf53b937&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;section-number-2&quot;&gt;4&lt;/span&gt; Chromium / Google Chrome&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;outline-text-2&quot; id=&quot;text-4&quot;&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;outline-container-org0b03b7b&quot; class=&quot;outline-3&quot;&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;org0b03b7b&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;section-number-3&quot;&gt;4.1&lt;/span&gt; Recommended chrome://flags&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;outline-container-org81a8dbc&quot; class=&quot;outline-3&quot;&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;org81a8dbc&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;section-number-3&quot;&gt;4.2&lt;/span&gt; How to use the KDE file picker instead of the default GTK file picker&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;outline-text-3&quot; id=&quot;text-4-2&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
The default file picker is the ugly GTK file picker, which can’t show thumbnails for images. The KDE file picker, kdialog, is much better; it has thumbnails and sorting abilities. Chrom{e, ium} won’t use kdialog unless you run it like this:
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;org-src-container&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;src src-bash&quot;&gt;$ env &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;&quot;&gt;XDG_CURRENT_DESKTOP&lt;/span&gt;=KDE chromium-browser
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
You can either modify Chromium’s .desktop entry to run this command or make this script:
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;org-src-container&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;src src-bash&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;&quot;&gt;#&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;&quot;&gt;!/bin/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;sh&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;export&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;&quot;&gt;XDG_CURRENT_DESKTOP&lt;/span&gt;=KDE
&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot;&gt;exec&lt;/span&gt; chromium-browser &lt;span style=&quot;font-style: italic;&quot;&gt;&quot;$@&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;outline-container-org8b65161&quot; class=&quot;outline-2&quot;&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;org8b65161&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;section-number-2&quot;&gt;5&lt;/span&gt; Emacs&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;outline-text-2&quot; id=&quot;text-5&quot;&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;org-ul&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;See my dotfiles/emacs.d repo&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take advantage of Language Server Protocol.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;outline-container-orge2dcf54&quot; class=&quot;outline-2&quot;&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;orge2dcf54&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;section-number-2&quot;&gt;6&lt;/span&gt; Hardware&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;outline-text-2&quot; id=&quot;text-6&quot;&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;outline-container-org40c22f6&quot; class=&quot;outline-3&quot;&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;org40c22f6&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;section-number-3&quot;&gt;6.1&lt;/span&gt; Reduce blue light from monitors&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;outline-text-3&quot; id=&quot;text-6-1&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Blue light is &lt;a href=&quot;https://phys.org/news/2018-08-chemists-blue.html&quot;&gt;harmful and permanently damaging to your retinas&lt;/a&gt;.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol class=&quot;org-ol&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Toggle the on-screen menu.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Find the screen for colors or color management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set any and all of these to 0
&lt;ol class=&quot;org-ol&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;blue&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;cyan&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;magenta&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
